ATHENS, Greeceâ€”An armed man broke into a bank in Piraeus on Monday (August 23rd) and took several people hostage before eventually surrendering to police. The man fired into the air several times, but no injuries are reported. According to initial information, three people stormed into the bank around noon. Two of them were arrested after they tried to escape, but the third returned to the bank, triggering the hostage situation. In addition to the gun, he told police he had a hand grenade. (Reuters, AP, AFP - 23/08/10)
